1
00:00:01,884 --> 00:00:04,768
<i>Pentagon officials continue
to deny any security breach</i>

2
00:00:04,790 --> 00:00:08,090
<i>and any responsibility
for the events of dark Thursday.</i>

3
00:00:08,471 --> 00:00:12,069
<i>Experts predicted the recovery
from dark Thursday will take years.</i>

4
00:00:12,151 --> 00:00:15,897
<i>But here in metropolis, the cleanup
effort has been remarkably swift.</i>

5
00:00:17,106 --> 00:00:20,817
<i>The public is stunned at how fast
rubble has been cleared from the streets.</i>

6
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,264
<i>This is Genevieve Sparling reporting live...</i>

7
00:00:24,695 --> 00:00:27,092
You've been out again all night, haven't you ?

8
00:00:27,515 --> 00:00:29,355
Can't do what I need to do in the daylight.

9
00:00:29,849 --> 00:00:32,396
Clark, I know you want to help, but...

10
00:00:33,247 --> 00:00:36,751
You can't single-handedly rebuild
everything that's been destroyed.

11
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:39,166
It's my mess, mom. I need to clean it up.

12
00:00:39,381 --> 00:00:41,784
You're not responsible for what happened.

13
00:00:41,962 --> 00:00:43,078
Zod is.

14
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,283
Zod would not have been released

15
00:00:46,427 --> 00:00:48,961
if, for once in my life, I had listened to Jor-El...

16
00:00:49,856 --> 00:00:51,663
and done what he asked me to do.

17
00:00:55,747 --> 00:00:57,463
I have chores to do.

18
00:00:57,486 --> 00:00:58,211
Hey.

19
00:00:59,388 --> 00:01:00,032
Hey.

20
00:01:01,407 --> 00:01:02,551
Are you okay ?

21
00:01:03,615 --> 00:01:04,682
Yeah, I’m fine.

22
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:06,522
Clark, wait, wait, wait.

23
00:01:08,106 --> 00:01:10,050
I’ve never seen you this worn out.

24
00:01:10,437 --> 00:01:12,393
Even you have your limits.

25
00:01:12,437 --> 00:01:14,021
The chores can wait.

26
00:01:14,088 --> 00:01:14,992
I’m okay.

27
00:01:15,717 --> 00:01:17,211
Really, I’m fine.

28
00:02:36,856 --> 00:02:38,381
"Sneeze"

29
00:03:36,336 --> 00:03:40,030
For someone about to change addresses,
You're travelling pretty light.

30
00:03:41,025 --> 00:03:44,103
Yeah. Well, I don't need a lot.
It's only temporary.

31
00:03:44,135 --> 00:03:46,791
They think the school should
reopen by next semester.

32
00:03:46,986 --> 00:03:50,063
It was nice of you to offer
me a room at the mansion.

33
00:03:50,096 --> 00:03:51,800
I don't know what I would have done.

34
00:03:56,925 --> 00:04:01,690
Lex, if you're not okay with this and
having second thoughts, then let's talk.

35
00:04:04,338 --> 00:04:07,070
There's nothing to talk about.
Everything's great.

36
00:04:21,876 --> 00:04:24,150
Clark, was that the first
time you ever sneezed ?

37
00:04:24,186 --> 00:04:27,900
Mm-Hmm, and the first time I’ve had a
scratchy throat with my ears all plugged up.

38
00:04:27,948 --> 00:04:30,371
- 98.6.
- No fever.

39
00:04:31,026 --> 00:04:33,750
I’m no doctor, but it seems
like it's just a common cold.

40
00:04:33,808 --> 00:04:38,930
You're far from common, Clark. I don't
remember you ever even having the sniffles.

41
00:04:39,228 --> 00:04:41,710
I’ve never pushed myself
so far into overdrive before.

42
00:04:41,735 --> 00:04:45,280
You said when you were in that
zone, your powers were gone.

43
00:04:45,305 --> 00:04:47,833
That means your immune system was normal.

44
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:49,993
You could have been exposed to something there.

45
00:04:50,368 --> 00:04:52,562
Whatever it is, I’m not really that sick.

46
00:04:54,755 --> 00:04:58,191
Hey. You guys are not gonna
believe what just happened to me.

47
00:04:58,225 --> 00:05:01,051
I’m out there jogging along,
minding my own business

48
00:05:01,097 --> 00:05:02,631
when, out of nowhere,

49
00:05:02,675 --> 00:05:06,291
a barn door comes falling from the
clear, blue sky and almost crushes me.

50
00:05:06,386 --> 00:05:07,772
How does that happen ?

51
00:05:10,287 --> 00:05:12,221
Maybe it fell from an airplane.

52
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:16,392
Good guess, but the only thing up there
was a severely traumatized sparrow.

53
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:22,791
Uh-Oh, does Clarky have the sniffles ?

54
00:05:24,238 --> 00:05:25,731
It's just a little cold.

55
00:05:26,745 --> 00:05:29,640
Well, lucky for you, I have the perfect remedy...

56
00:05:29,665 --> 00:05:32,671
honey and a little bit of cayenne pepper.
Works every time.

57
00:05:32,828 --> 00:05:35,572
First you sneeze a bunch of times,
but then you're pretty much cured.

58
00:05:35,595 --> 00:05:36,712
Lois, I’ll pass.

59
00:05:36,755 --> 00:05:39,001
I think we're all out of cayenne, Lois.

60
00:05:41,407 --> 00:05:44,931
No, you're not. I’m gonna whip up
a little bit of something here.

61
00:05:50,356 --> 00:05:52,040
Where did your barn door go ?

62
00:05:52,198 --> 00:05:55,870
It was here late last night when I came
to drop off the documents, and now it's gone.

63
00:05:57,217 --> 00:05:58,910
Look at that. It is gone.

64
00:06:00,115 --> 00:06:02,382
And it's been ripped right off its hinges.

65
00:06:04,335 --> 00:06:06,941
Oh, my god, that barn door.
I knew it looked familiar.

66
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:08,641
Now, how in the world does that happen ?

67
00:06:21,716 --> 00:06:24,940
Mr. Pontius. What the
hell am I paying you for ?

68
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:28,091
I was followed again today.

69
00:06:28,127 --> 00:06:30,662
Black range rover, edge city plates ?

70
00:06:31,418 --> 00:06:34,460
I tracked it to an abandoned factory
on 5th and Hayworth.

71
00:06:34,577 --> 00:06:36,213
Why are you still here ?

72
00:06:37,597 --> 00:06:38,831
I’m on my way.

73
00:06:40,606 --> 00:06:43,821
I want this taken care of
by any means necessary.

74
00:06:44,466 --> 00:06:45,522
Do you understand ?

75
00:06:53,328 --> 00:06:56,303
I had no idea I was moving into a fortress.

76
00:06:57,226 --> 00:06:59,733
Everywhere I turn, there's another security guard.

77
00:07:01,236 --> 00:07:03,992
Lana, that gentleman's not a security guard.

78
00:07:04,995 --> 00:07:07,121
He's a private investigator.

79
00:07:09,277 --> 00:07:12,540
Over the last few days, it's
become clear I’m being followed.

80
00:07:12,845 --> 00:07:13,773
By who ?

81
00:07:15,055 --> 00:07:19,891
Well, I doubt I have to look much further
than the lowest branch in the family tree, but...

82
00:07:20,336 --> 00:07:23,071
- I can't be sure.
- Have you called the police ?

83
00:07:23,816 --> 00:07:26,580
After breaking every law imaginable
while I was inhabited by Zod,

84
00:07:26,605 --> 00:07:28,953
I don't want to go anywhere near a badge.

85
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:33,100
I can't trust anyone, not even my own security.

86
00:07:35,485 --> 00:07:37,120
You can trust me.

87
00:07:40,485 --> 00:07:41,781
Of course I can.

88
00:07:44,135 --> 00:07:45,733
And I want you to have this...

89
00:07:47,928 --> 00:07:49,741
In case of an emergency.

90
00:07:51,878 --> 00:07:54,072
He's the best P. I. in Metropolis.

91
00:07:54,406 --> 00:07:57,660
If anything happens to me,
you need to call that number,

92
00:07:57,908 --> 00:07:59,190
Not the police.

93
00:07:59,415 --> 00:08:01,572
Robert Pontius will make sure you're safe.

94
00:08:01,608 --> 00:08:03,311
Lex, don't talk like that.

95
00:08:04,157 --> 00:08:06,020
I’m just being cautious.

96
00:08:22,325 --> 00:08:23,190
Chloe...

97
00:08:23,226 --> 00:08:25,972
How's this for a megadose of guilt money ?

98
00:08:26,505 --> 00:08:29,882
Well, uh...
I’ve got bigger news.

99
00:08:30,096 --> 00:08:32,390
What happened ? Is everything all right ?

100
00:08:33,886 --> 00:08:35,100
I sneezed.

101
00:08:37,537 --> 00:08:38,381
And ?

102
00:08:38,707 --> 00:08:40,423
And ? Chloe, that's not normal.

103
00:08:40,455 --> 00:08:43,501
Clark, nothing with you is exactly normal,

104
00:08:43,527 --> 00:08:45,613
But  I wouldn't call sneezing today's headline.

105
00:08:45,638 --> 00:08:47,440
You don't understand. I...

106
00:08:48,326 --> 00:08:49,150
I  was...

107
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,122
You what ?
Grab a tissue and get over it.

108
00:09:00,798 --> 00:09:01,872
Gesundheit.

109
00:09:03,606 --> 00:09:05,710
I tried to warn you.
I’ve come down with some sort of cold.

110
00:09:05,728 --> 00:09:08,003
And become a walking air cannon.

111
00:09:08,045 --> 00:09:10,322
Let's get you out of here before you blow again.

112
00:09:10,347 --> 00:09:12,991
At least I was able to cover half my face that time.
This morning I...

113
00:09:13,437 --> 00:09:16,112
I blew the barn door halfway across small county.

114
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:17,642
It almost hit Lois.

115
00:09:17,917 --> 00:09:19,341
Lois, as in Lane ?

116
00:09:19,457 --> 00:09:21,883
Now she's on a one-woman
crusade to find an explanation.

117
00:09:21,918 --> 00:09:24,141
You know her. She won't
stop digging until she hits china.

118
00:09:24,178 --> 00:09:27,600
I’ll take care of Lois.
You just take care of that cold.

119
00:09:27,637 --> 00:09:29,361
We have enough natural
disasters around here

120
00:09:29,385 --> 00:09:32,411
Without having to worry about hurricane
Clark looming off the coast.

121
00:09:32,568 --> 00:09:33,250
No !

122
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:36,962
Just kidding.

123
00:09:50,078 --> 00:09:53,122
Well, I forgot what a
concerned parent you are.

124
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:55,443
That's why you're having
me followed, isn't it ?

125
00:09:55,475 --> 00:09:57,880
To make sure I don't destroy
the rest of the world ?

126
00:09:58,145 --> 00:10:00,681
If I were having you followed, son,

127
00:10:01,006 --> 00:10:03,170
You would never know it.
I can guarantee you that.

128
00:10:03,196 --> 00:10:06,310
I hate to disappoint you, but
whatever powers I had are long gone.

129
00:10:06,338 --> 00:10:09,210
So if you're looking for an encore
performance, you're out of luck.

130
00:10:09,257 --> 00:10:10,903
Elvis has left the building.

131
00:10:10,948 --> 00:10:13,012
You want to find out who's stalking you ?

132
00:10:13,295 --> 00:10:14,941
I suggest you concentrate

133
00:10:14,956 --> 00:10:20,103
On remembering every little
minute detail of that horrific day.

134
00:10:21,047 --> 00:10:23,281
Well, I guess I should have kept a blog...

135
00:10:23,328 --> 00:10:26,342
because I suffered a total memory loss.

136
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,942
Besides what Lana has told
me, those 24 hours are gone.

137
00:10:32,085 --> 00:10:34,743
The atrocities you committed...

138
00:10:34,788 --> 00:10:38,242
they could have been witnessed by anyone.
Lex, please, let me help you.

139
00:10:38,475 --> 00:10:41,673
I’ve been on the receiving end of your
help before, Dad. I think I’ll pass.

140
00:10:45,276 --> 00:10:50,462
Listen to me. There are some adversaries
that cannot be defeated alone !

141
00:10:52,778 --> 00:10:54,051
Lex ! Lex !

142
00:11:37,437 --> 00:11:39,981
The bear is hibernating, over.

143
00:11:52,297 --> 00:11:53,433
How you doing ?

144
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:57,116
This is one part about being human I don't envy.

145
00:11:57,711 --> 00:11:59,204
It's not all that bad.

146
00:11:59,242 --> 00:12:01,518
You can lie on the couch
all day and watch DVDs

147
00:12:01,556 --> 00:12:04,363
While your mom makes some
doctor-certified chicken soup.

148
00:12:04,406 --> 00:12:08,163
Mom, I can watch DVDs after
I fix the irrigation ditch.

149
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:11,673
No, your health is a lot more important
than the irrigation ditch.

150
00:12:12,318 --> 00:12:16,540
You're in uncharted waters now, Clark,
and your dad's not here to help us out, so...

151
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:20,392
please, you have to trust
my instincts and rest.

152
00:12:21,095 --> 00:12:21,841
Okay ?

153
00:12:26,856 --> 00:12:27,792
Lionel.

154
00:12:28,395 --> 00:12:29,661
Is everything all right ?

155
00:12:29,985 --> 00:12:30,771
Lex.

156
00:12:31,258 --> 00:12:33,551
He's gone. I think he's been abducted.

157
00:12:36,096 --> 00:12:37,443
Who do you think's behind it ?

158
00:12:39,118 --> 00:12:43,063
Considering what he stole from the pentagon,
my initial reaction was the, uh...

159
00:12:43,506 --> 00:12:48,400
government, But after I spoke to my
contacts in Washington, I don't think so.

160
00:12:50,046 --> 00:12:51,661
You have to find him, Clark.

161
00:12:51,696 --> 00:12:54,931
Why ? Lex and I have nothing to
do with each other anymore.

162
00:12:54,967 --> 00:12:56,703
But you and Zod do.

163
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:03,382
Lex insists he can't remember anything that
happened when he was possessed by Zod,

164
00:13:03,418 --> 00:13:07,842
But he might not be honest about it.
He might remember it all.

165
00:13:08,265 --> 00:13:13,101
Whoever his captors are, if they put enough
pressure on him, he could tell the truth...

166
00:13:14,226 --> 00:13:15,272
about you.

167
00:13:33,136 --> 00:13:36,022
Well, good morning, Mr. Invincible.

168
00:13:38,308 --> 00:13:39,332
Where am I ?

169
00:13:40,147 --> 00:13:43,313
In your cage, where every lab rat belongs.

170
00:13:44,147 --> 00:13:46,813
Oh, and before you even try escaping,

171
00:13:46,858 --> 00:13:50,872
You might want to consider you're hooked up
to enough wattage to drop an elephant.

172
00:13:50,917 --> 00:13:51,863
Who are you ?

173
00:13:52,817 --> 00:13:57,321
Just someone who's interested in how
you possess superhuman powers.

174
00:13:59,118 --> 00:14:00,082
Powers ?

175
00:14:02,276 --> 00:14:04,271
I don't know what you're talking about.

176
00:14:04,628 --> 00:14:07,332
Oh, come on, Lex !

177
00:14:07,557 --> 00:14:09,953
We both know you were
the one at the Pentagon,

178
00:14:09,986 --> 00:14:13,073
swatting away those bullets
like they were mosquitoes...

179
00:14:13,338 --> 00:14:15,573
and not even a scratch.

180
00:14:16,236 --> 00:14:17,521
Yeah, see, we...

181
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:21,402
We saw it on the only working
satellite on dark Thursday.

182
00:14:21,446 --> 00:14:25,130
So we know you have the powers.

183
00:14:25,736 --> 00:14:27,672
We kind of want to know how you got them.

184
00:14:28,268 --> 00:14:30,262
My people are already onto you.

185
00:14:31,527 --> 00:14:32,833
Your people ?

186
00:14:34,388 --> 00:14:38,932
I  think that's the guy that I caught
kind of roaming around outside.

187
00:14:38,968 --> 00:14:40,171
Pontius, right ?

188
00:14:40,715 --> 00:14:43,252
That's the guy with the bullet in his head.

189
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:47,483
Enough foreplay.

190
00:14:47,735 --> 00:14:50,141
All right ? Let's get this started.

191
00:14:50,655 --> 00:14:52,363
You're gonna tell me everything.

192
00:15:04,758 --> 00:15:08,180
See, I told you. I am no chicken
little, and that is no acorn.

193
00:15:08,226 --> 00:15:08,951
Whoa.

194
00:15:09,505 --> 00:15:12,883
How is that even remotely conceivable ?
The Kents live miles away from here.

195
00:15:12,917 --> 00:15:15,242
It's definitely weird. I’ll give you that.

196
00:15:15,287 --> 00:15:19,031
But it's not "wall of weird."
It's called a microburst.

197
00:15:19,276 --> 00:15:20,492
Micro what ?

198
00:15:20,526 --> 00:15:25,233
It's like a sudden, mini tornado. It happens when
there are extreme changes In the temperature.

199
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:27,933
It's actually not that unheard
of in the Midwest.

200
00:15:28,017 --> 00:15:31,241
It was sunny and 75. There was
nothing extreme about the weather.

201
00:15:31,266 --> 00:15:35,093
Well, you might not have felt it. It was
probably in the upper atmosphere. But

202
00:15:35,135 --> 00:15:39,022
there must have been some sort of
change in the barometric pressures.

203
00:15:39,615 --> 00:15:42,370
Either you've been watching too much weather channel

204
00:15:42,428 --> 00:15:45,510
or a year at the daily planet has
turned you into a hardened sceptic.

205
00:15:45,538 --> 00:15:48,622
It's called being realistic.
You might want to try it once in a while.

206
00:15:48,665 --> 00:15:50,332
You were the one who always told me

207
00:15:50,378 --> 00:15:53,360
that science can explain only a fraction
of what happens in this crazy town.

208
00:15:53,387 --> 00:15:56,303
And this happens to fall into that fraction.

209
00:15:56,356 --> 00:15:58,911
Look, Lois, I still believe in
the paranormal. Trust me.

210
00:15:58,948 --> 00:16:02,540
But you have to accept the fact that
sometimes the answers you're looking for

211
00:16:02,566 --> 00:16:05,693
are no further away than the front
pages of your scientific American.

212
00:16:17,886 --> 00:16:19,723
What are you doing with the gun ?

213
00:16:20,946 --> 00:16:23,571
We were specifically told not to use violence.

214
00:16:24,156 --> 00:16:25,001
So  ?

215
00:16:25,405 --> 00:16:28,762
I don't answer to anybody, okay ?
Especially your boss.

216
00:16:29,195 --> 00:16:33,561
What I want to know is how bullets bounced
off his body like ping-pong balls.

217
00:16:34,648 --> 00:16:38,062
Now, information like that is very
valuable on the open market.

218
00:16:39,607 --> 00:16:41,631
You were specifically hired to...

219
00:16:41,656 --> 00:16:42,703
Yeah, well, guess what ?

220
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,742
I’m an entrepreneur, okay ?

221
00:16:46,136 --> 00:16:50,593
So either you join my newest venture,
or you can end up like the Pontius guy.

222
00:16:51,157 --> 00:16:52,262
Your choice.

223
00:16:58,246 --> 00:16:59,011
Hey, Lex !

224
00:17:01,287 --> 00:17:05,211
Hey, I was thinking. Why don't
we try a little experiment ?

225
00:17:05,748 --> 00:17:06,893
What are you doing ?

226
00:17:07,527 --> 00:17:10,122
I told you, I don't remember
any of what's happening.

227
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:13,953
Yeah, but it did. And I want
to see it happen again.

228
00:17:13,987 --> 00:17:15,721
Please don't. No.

229
00:17:18,436 --> 00:17:19,851
Oh, God !

230
00:17:37,376 --> 00:17:38,122
Lois...

231
00:17:38,617 --> 00:17:40,071
What are you doing here ?

232
00:17:40,275 --> 00:17:43,562
I wanted to personally hand-deliver
this article to your editor.

233
00:17:43,697 --> 00:17:46,093
An article ? You're a journalist now ?

234
00:17:46,488 --> 00:17:47,232
Yeah.

235
00:17:47,378 --> 00:17:50,251
Wow ! That's a lot of words.

236
00:17:51,065 --> 00:17:55,833
Well, the Smallville Ledger was way too small-minded
to appreciate investigative reportage, so

237
00:17:55,868 --> 00:17:58,342
I thought the Planet would
be the perfect publisher.

238
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:02,350
Lois, I hate to be the one
to rain on your Pulitzer parade,

239
00:18:02,397 --> 00:18:06,180
But I really don't think
that a story about weather

240
00:18:06,218 --> 00:18:09,402
Is gonna stand a chance when we're still dealing
with the aftermath of dark Thursday.

241
00:18:09,426 --> 00:18:13,173
No, this story is way more
than about wild weather, okay ?

242
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:16,043
Not only is it an exposé
